=3D"0">A <b data-path-to-node=3D"0" data-index-in-node=3D"2">Media Kit</b> =
is a digital CV for an influencer. In the beauty industry, where visual aes=
thetic and data-driven ROI are equally important, these kits act as a pitch=
 deck to convince brand managers and agencies that a creator is worth the i=
nvestment.</p><hr data-path-to-node=3D"1"><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"2">Core =
Components of a 2026 Beauty Media Kit</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"3">A prof=
essional media kit typically consists of 3=E2=80=935 pages and includes the=
 following sections:</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"4">1. The "Bio" and Brand =
Identity</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"5"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"5,0,0"=
><b data-path-to-node=3D"5,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Pitch:</b> A s=
hort summary of the creator's "niche" (e.g., "High-end bridal makeup specia=
list" or "Science-backed clinical skincare").</p></li><li><p data-path-to-n=
ode=3D"5,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"5,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Visua=
l Aesthetic:</b> High-resolution imagery that demonstrates their production=
 quality and "look."</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"6">2. Verified A=
udience Demographics</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"7">Since this data is priv=
ate (not in the public API), creators take screenshots or use API-linked pl=
atforms to prove:</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"8"><li><p data-path-to-node=
=3D"8,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"8,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Age and =
Gender:</b> Essential for beauty brands (e.g., a brand launching a "men=E2=
=80=99s grooming line" needs to see a high male percentage).</p></li><li><p=
 data-path-to-node=3D"8,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"8,1,0" data-index-in-n=
ode=3D"0">Geographic Split:</b> Brands often only ship to specific regions =
(UK/US/EU), so they need to see where the viewers live.</p></li><li><p data=
-path-to-node=3D"8,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"8,2,0" data-index-in-node=
=3D"0">Top Interests:</b> Shows what else the audience buys (e.g., "Sustain=
ability," "Luxury Fashion").</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"9">3. Pe=
rformance Benchmarks (The "Proof")</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"10">This sec=
tion fills the gaps of the public YouTube API:</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"=
11"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"11,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"11,0,0" dat=
a-index-in-node=3D"0">Average View Duration (AVD):</b> Proves people actual=
ly watch the videos.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"11,1,0"><b data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"11,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Click-Through Rate (CTR):</b=
> Shows how effective the creator's thumbnails and titles are.</p></li><li>=
<p data-path-to-node=3D"11,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"11,2,0" data-index-=
